From 623fa61324c72cc2f4d4dcbd6281520e13da769d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Avula Sri Charan <asrichar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 22 Aug 2025 10:18:27 +0530
Subject: UPSTREAM:PLATFORM:wifi:ath12k: remove the soc from group only when recovery is enabled

In case of Firmware crash when recovery is not enabled the RDDM dumps
for all the SOC's have to be collected for which ag->num_started is
used to know how many SOC's are started so that upon collecting those
many dumps host will issue a BUG_ON().

But currently in reset_work the SOC is detached from the group and
num_probed is decremented, because of which BUG_ON will be invoked
without collecting all SOC's dump.

Fix this by not calling ath12k_core_to_group_ref_put() when recovery
is not enabled so that the core won't be detached from group and the
rddm dump for all SOC's can be copied.

Signed-off-by: Avula Sri Charan <asrichar@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c | 7 ++++---
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
@@ -3691,10 +3691,11 @@ static void ath12k_core_reset(struct wor
 
 	/* UMAC RESET relies on ag->num_started as barrier to make sure
 	 * umac related interrupts are received from all non-asserted chips
-	 * before writing to the shared memory. So need to decrement the
-	 * before trigerring umac reset.
+	 * before writing to the shared memory. So need to decrement it
+	 * when recovery is enabled before triggering umac reset.
 	 */
-	ath12k_core_to_group_ref_put(ab);
+	if (ab->fw_recovery_support)
+		ath12k_core_to_group_ref_put(ab);
 
 	if (ag->recovery_mode != ATH12K_MLO_RECOVERY_MODE0) {
 		if (ath12k_core_trigger_umac_reset(ab, WMI_MLO_TEARDOWN_SSR_REASON) ||
